In CLEVE's Synopsis‚ Navicula anqulosa is considered to be a mere variety of N. palpebralis, but N. solida to be a distinct species, recognised at the median striae being alter- nately longer and shorter. As DONKIN's original figure of N. anyulosa just shows that kind of striation, I think GRE- GORY's and CLEVE's forms must be united and specifically distinguished from Navio-ula palpebralis. The fossil specimen I have seen being distinctly apiculate, I have drawn it in f. 23.
